laboratory_examinations.findings: Ill-defined 4.6 x 6.7 x 5.5 cm lesion superior to the expected location of the appendix, with thickened, irregular and enhancing peripheral margins, no hemorrhage, trace free fluid in the right lower quadrant, no noticeable obstruction, normal liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, gallbladder, and no lymphadenopathy.
